<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">QUESTIONS AND ANSWERS</font></u></b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.35pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Q1:</font></b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><b>With the year half over, how is the macro-economic environment impacting the industries you serve and how does it compare with your expectations at the beginning of 2015?</b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.35pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A:</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Overall, our view of the world has not changed much since our original outlook in January&nbsp;of 2015.&#160; Our expectations for world economic growth for the year are similar to what we expected in January.&#160; As we expected, mining continues to be severely depressed, construction-related sales in China and Brazil are substantially lower than 2014 and orders related to oil and gas are down significantly which will likely lead to lower sales in the second half of 2015.</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.35pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Q2:</font></b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><b>Has the recent situation in Greece had significant impact on your business?</b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.35pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A:</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Greece is not significant to Caterpillar&#146;s financial results.&#160; It appears there has been a short-term resolution to the situation and hopefully Greece can now turn its attention to growth.</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.35pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Q3:</font></b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><b>Can you discuss changes in dealer inventories in the second quarter of 2015?&#160; What are your expectations for the full year of 2015?</b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.35pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A:</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Dealer machine and engine inventories decreased about $300 million in the second quarter of 2015 and about $500 million in the second quarter of 2014.</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">During the first six months of 2015, dealer machine and engine inventories increased about $600 million.&#160; We expect dealers will reduce inventories during the remainder of 2015, resulting in lower year-end inventories in 2015 compared to 2014.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.35pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Q4:</font></b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><b>Can you comment on your expectations for Caterpillar inventory for the remainder of 2015?</b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.35pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A:</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Our inventory decreased in the second quarter, and we expect additional declines during the remainder of 2015 as a result of our continued focus on operational improvements and slightly lower sales.</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.35pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Q5:</font></b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><b>Can you discuss how lower oil prices have impacted your second-quarter sales and your expectations for the remainder of 2015?</b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.35pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A:</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Some decline in sales related to oil occurred in the second quarter, primarily in well servicing and drilling with some impact to machinery for oil and gas-related construction.&#160; Order rates began to decline in the second half of 2014 and have continued into 2015.&#160; We expect a more significant decline in oil-related sales during the second half of 2015 as the order backlog declines.</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.35pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Q6:</font></b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><b>Can you comment on your order backlog by segment?</b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.35pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A:</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>At the end of the second quarter of 2015, the order backlog was $14.8 billion.&#160; This represents about a $1.7 billion reduction from the end of the first quarter of 2015.&#160; About half of the decrease was in Construction Industries.&#160; In addition, the order backlog for both Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation and Resource Industries declined.</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.0pt;text-indent:-27.0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Q7:</font></b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><b>Can you comment on expense related to your short-term incentive compensation plans?</b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.35pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A:</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Short-term incentive compensation expense is directly related to financial and operational performance measured against targets set annually.&#160; The second-quarter expense related to 2015 was about $200 million, and we expect the full year will be about $830 million.&#160; Short-term incentive compensation in the second quarter of 2014 was about $360 million, and full-year 2014 was about $1.3 billion.</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.35pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Q8:</font></b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><b>Can you comment on your balance sheet and ME&amp;T operating cash flow in the second quarter of 2015?</b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A:</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>ME&amp;T operating cash flow for the second quarter of 2015 was $1.638 billion, compared with $2.064 billion in the second quarter of 2014.&#160; The decline was primarily due to lower profit.&#160; The top cash deployment priority is to maintain a strong financial position to support our credit rating.&#160; As such, the ME&amp;T debt-to-</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;">15<a name="PB_15_231022_6447"></a></p>
<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="3" width="100%" noshade align="left" style="color:#010101;"></div>
</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='15',FILE='C:\JMS\109208\15-14853-1\task7500473\14853-1-mm-09.htm',USER='109208',CD='Jul 23 04:18 2015' -->

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">capital ratio was 35.8 percent, improved from 37.4 percent at the end of 2014.&#160; Our cash and liquidity positions also remain strong with an enterprise cash balance of $7.821 billion as of June&nbsp;30, 2015.&#160; Additionally, cash will be used to support growth, appropriately fund employee benefit plans, pay dividends and repurchase common stock.&#160; During the second quarter, capital expenditures totaled $0.3 billion and the quarterly dividend payment was $0.4 billion.&#160; We further demonstrated our commitment to deliver superior returns to stockholders through the business cycles with the announcement to increase the quarterly cash dividend by 10 percent to $0.77 per share of common stock.&#160; Through dividends and the repurchase of approximately $0.5 billion of common stock, we returned a total of about $1.4 billion to stockholders in the first half of 2015.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Q9:</font></b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><b>Can you provide an update on your cash deployment and stock repurchase plans for 2015?</b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A:</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>In the first quarter of 2014, the Board of Directors approved a $10.0 billion authorization, which expires in December&nbsp;2018.&#160; At the end of the second quarter of 2015, we had $7.0 billion remaining in the authorization.&#160; Our strong balance sheet and cash position provide us the ability to repurchase additional stock, and we intend to repurchase $1.5 billion of common stock during the third quarter of 2015.</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Caterpillar&#146;s cash deployment priorities for uses of cash have not changed.&#160; Higher cash deployment priorities will be funded first, and stock repurchase remains the last priority.&#160; Stock repurchase plans are always subject to the company&#146;s cash deployment priorities and can change based on business and market conditions.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.0pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Q10:</font></b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><b>Over the last six months there have been several Caterpillar public releases related to &#147;micro-grids,&#148; &#147;internet of things,&#148; &#147;peer-to-peer rental&#148; and even the formation of a new Analytics and Innovation Division.&#160; Is this a change in direction or strategy?</b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 27.35pt;text-indent:-27.0pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A:</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>While not a change in our strategy, we are accelerating our focus on emerging technologies.&#160; We intend to embrace these technologies to better execute our strategy and help our customers succeed.&#160; This year we also established an Analytics and Innovation Division. The division will leverage the combined efforts of the company&#146;s various technology areas, while pushing for more innovation and change management.&#160; By focusing internally as well as partnering with and investing in other companies, we are continuing to challenge ourselves to better position the company for the future.</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;">16<a name="PB_16_231129_7056"></a></p>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">GLOSSARY OF TERMS</font></u></b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse;">
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">1.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Across   the Table </font></b>&#151; A joint   initiative with Caterpillar and its dealers to identify, build and strengthen   capabilities necessary to meet the diverse and changing needs of our   customers. The focus is on leveraging demonstrated best practices to improve   performance on delivering an exceptional customer experience.</p>    </td>   </tr>
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">2.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">All   Other Segments</font></b> &#151; Primarily includes activities such as: the   remanufacturing of Cat&#174; engines and components and remanufacturing services   for other companies as well as the business strategy, product management,   development, manufacturing, marketing and product support of undercarriage,   specialty products, hardened bar stock components and ground engaging tools   primarily for Cat products, paving products, forestry products and industrial   and waste products; the product management, development, marketing, sales and   product support of on-highway vocational trucks for North America; parts   distribution; distribution services responsible for dealer development and   administration including a wholly owned dealer in Japan, dealer portfolio   management and ensuring the most efficient and effective distribution of   machines, engines and parts.</p>    </td>   </tr>
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">3.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Consolidating   Adjustments</font></b> &#151; Elimination of transactions between   Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation and Financial Products.</p>    </td>   </tr>
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">4.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Construction   Industries</font></b> &#151; A segment primarily responsible for supporting   customers using machinery in infrastructure and building construction   applications. Responsibilities include business strategy, product design,   product management and development, manufacturing, marketing and sales and   product support. The product portfolio includes backhoe loaders, small wheel   loaders, small track-type tractors, skid steer loaders, multi-terrain   loaders, mini excavators, compact wheel loaders, telehandlers, select work tools,   small, medium and large track excavators, wheel excavators, medium wheel   loaders, compact track loaders, medium track-type tractors, track-type   loaders, motor graders, pipelayers and mid-tier soil compactors. In addition,   Construction Industries has responsibility for an integrated manufacturing   cost center.</p>    </td>   </tr>
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">5.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Currency</font></b>   &#151; With respect to sales and revenues, currency represents the translation   impact on sales resulting from changes in foreign currency exchange rates   versus the U.S. dollar. With respect to operating profit, currency represents   the net translation impact on sales and operating costs resulting from   changes in foreign currency exchange rates versus the U.S. dollar. Currency   includes the impact on sales and operating profit for the Machinery,   Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation lines of business only; currency impacts on   Financial Products&#146; revenues and operating profit are included in the   Financial Products&#146; portions of the respective analyses. With respect to   other income/expense, currency represents the effects of forward and option   contracts entered into by the company to reduce the risk of fluctuations in   exchange rates (hedging) and the net effect of changes in foreign currency   exchange rates on our foreign currency assets and liabilities for consolidated   results (translation).</p>    </td>   </tr>
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">6.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Debt-to-Capital   Ratio</font></b> &#151; A key measure of Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp;   Transportation&#146;s financial strength used by both management and our credit   rating agencies. The metric is defined as Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp;   Transportation&#146;s short-term borrowings, long-term debt due within one year   and long-term debt due after one year (debt) divided by the sum of Machinery,   Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation&#146;s debt and stockholders&#146; equity. Debt also   includes Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation&#146;s borrowings from   Financial Products.</p>    </td>   </tr>
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">7.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">EAME</font></b>   &#151; A geographic region including Europe, Africa, the Middle East and the   Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS).</p>    </td>   </tr>
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">8.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Earning   Assets</font></b> &#151; Assets consisting primarily of total finance   receivables net of unearned income, plus equipment on operating leases, less   accumulated depreciation at Cat Financial.</p>    </td>   </tr>
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">9.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Energy&nbsp;&amp;   Transportation </font></b>(formerly   Power Systems) &#151; A segment primarily responsible for supporting   customers using reciprocating engines, turbines, diesel-electric locomotives   and related parts across industries serving power generation, industrial, oil   and gas and transportation applications, including marine and rail-related   businesses. Responsibilities include business strategy, product design,   product management, development, manufacturing, marketing, sales and product   support of turbines and turbine-related services, reciprocating engine   powered generator sets, integrated systems used in the electric power   generation industry, reciprocating engines and integrated systems and   solutions for the marine and oil and gas industries; reciprocating engines   supplied to the industrial industry as well as Cat machinery; the business   strategy, product design, product management, development, manufacturing,   remanufacturing, leasing and service of diesel-electric locomotives and   components and other rail-related products and services.</p>    </td>   </tr>  </table>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;">17<a name="PB_17_231249_5796"></a></p>

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse;">
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">10.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Financial   Products Segment </font></b>&#151; Provides financing to customers and   dealers for the purchase and lease of Cat and other equipment, as well as   some financing for Caterpillar sales to dealers. Financing plans include   operating and finance leases, installment sale contracts, working capital   loans and wholesale financing plans. The segment also provides various forms   of insurance to customers and dealers to help support the purchase and lease   of our equipment. Financial Products Segment profit is determined on a pretax   basis and includes other income/expense items.</p>    </td>   </tr>
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">11.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Latin   America</font></b> &#151; A geographic region including Central and South   American countries and Mexico.</p>    </td>   </tr>
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">12.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Lean   Management</font></b> &#151; A holistic management system that uses a   sequential cadence of principles to drive the highest quality and lowest   total cost to achieve customer requirements.</p>    </td>   </tr>
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">13.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Machinery,   Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation (ME&amp;T)</font></b> &#151; Represents   the aggregate total of Construction Industries, Resource Industries, Energy&nbsp;&amp;   Transportation and All Other Segments and related corporate items and   eliminations.</p>    </td>   </tr>
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">14.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Machinery,   Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation Other Operating (Income) Expenses </font></b>&#151; Comprised primarily of gains/losses on   disposal of long-lived assets, gains/losses on divestitures, long-lived asset   impairment charges and legal settlements. Restructuring costs, which are   classified as other operating expenses on the Results of Operations, are   presented separately on the Operating Profit Comparison.</p>    </td>   </tr>
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">15.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Manufacturing   Costs </font></b>&#151;   Manufacturing costs exclude the impacts of currency and represent the   volume-adjusted change for variable costs and the absolute dollar change for   period manufacturing costs. Variable manufacturing costs are defined as   having a direct relationship with the volume of production. This includes   material costs, direct labor and other costs that vary directly with   production volume such as freight, power to operate machines and supplies   that are consumed in the manufacturing process. Period manufacturing costs   support production but are defined as generally not having a direct   relationship to short-term changes in volume. Examples include machinery and   equipment repair, depreciation on manufacturing assets, facility support,   procurement, factory scheduling, manufacturing planning and operations   management.</p>    </td>   </tr>
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">16.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Price   Realization</font></b> &#151; The   impact of net price changes excluding currency and new product introductions.   Price realization includes the impact of changes in the relative weighting of   sales between geographic regions.</p>    </td>   </tr>
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">17.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Resource   Industries </font></b>&#151; A segment primarily responsible for supporting   customers using machinery in mining and quarrying applications.   Responsibilities include business strategy, product design, product   management and development, manufacturing, marketing and sales and product   support. The product portfolio includes large track-type tractors, large   mining trucks, hard rock vehicles, longwall miners, electric rope shovels,   draglines, hydraulic shovels, drills, highwall miners, large wheel loaders,   off-highway trucks, articulated trucks, wheel tractor scrapers, wheel dozers,   select work tools, machinery components and electronics and control systems.   Resource Industries also manages areas that provide services to other parts of   the company, including integrated manufacturing and research and development.   In addition, segment profit includes the impact from divestiture of portions   of the Bucyrus distribution business.</p>    </td>   </tr>
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">18.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Restructuring Costs</font></b>   &#151; Primarily costs for employee separation costs and long-lived asset   impairments.</p>    </td>   </tr>
<tr>
<td width="5%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:5.28%;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">19.</font></p>    </td>
<td width="94%" valign="top" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:94.72%;">
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Sales   Volume</font></b> &#151; With respect to sales and revenues, sales volume   represents the impact of changes in the quantities sold for Machinery,   Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation as well as the incremental revenue impact of   new product introductions, including emissions-related product updates. With   respect to operating profit, sales volume represents the impact of changes in   the quantities sold for Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation combined   with product mix as well as the net operating profit impact of new product   introductions, including emissions-related product updates. Product mix   represents the net operating profit impact of changes in the relative   weighting of Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation sales with respect   to total sales.</p>    </td>   </tr>  </table>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;">18<a name="PB_18_231256_2897"></a></p>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">
<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">NON-GAAP FINANCIAL MEASURES</font></u></b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The following definition is provided for &#147;non-GAAP financial measures&#148; in connection with Regulation G issued by the Securities and Exchange Commission.&#160; This non-GAAP financial measure has no standardized meaning prescribed by U.S. GAAP and therefore is unlikely to be comparable to the calculation of similar measures for other companies.&#160; Management does not intend this item to be considered in isolation or substituted for the related GAAP measure.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Profit Per Share Excluding Restructuring Costs</font></u></b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">We incurred restructuring costs in 2014 and in the first and second quarters of 2015 and expect to incur additional restructuring costs in the second half of 2015.&#160; We believe it is important to separately quantify the profit per share impact of restructuring costs in order for our second-quarter 2015 results and the 2015 outlook to be meaningful to our readers.&#160; We have also provided 2014 profit per share excluding restructuring costs comparable to the 2015 presentation.&#160; Reconciliation of profit per share excluding restructuring costs to the most directly comparable GAAP measure, profit per share, is as follows:</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse;">
<tr>
<td width="49%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:49.0%;">

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation</font></u></b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Caterpillar defines Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation as it is presented in the supplemental data as Caterpillar Inc. and its subsidiaries with Financial Products accounted for on the equity basis.&#160; Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation information relates to the design, manufacture and marketing of our products.&#160; Financial Products&#146; information relates to the financing to customers and dealers for the purchase and lease of Caterpillar and other equipment.&#160; The nature of these businesses is different, especially with regard to the financial position and cash flow items.&#160; Caterpillar management utilizes this presentation internally to highlight these differences.&#160; We also believe this presentation will assist readers in understanding our business.&#160; Pages&nbsp;20-28 reconcile Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation with Financial Products on the equity basis to Caterpillar Inc. consolidated financial information.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Caterpillar&#146;s latest financial results and outlook are also available via:</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Telephone:</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">800-228-7717 (Inside the United States and Canada)</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">858-764-9492 (Outside the United States and Canada)</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">http://www.caterpillar.com/en/investors.html</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman"><font style="font-size:10.0pt;">http://www.caterpillar.com/en/investors/quarterly-results.html</font> (live broadcast/replays of quarterly conference call)</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><hr size="1" width="25%" noshade align="left" style="color:black;"></div>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 12.25pt;text-indent:-12.25pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">1</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Represents Caterpillar Inc. and its subsidiaries with Financial Products accounted for on the equity basis.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 12.25pt;text-indent:-12.25pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">2</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of Financial Products&#146; revenues earned from Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 12.25pt;text-indent:-12.25pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">3</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of net expenses recorded by Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation paid to Financial Products.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 12.25pt;text-indent:-12.25pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">4</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of interest expense recorded between Financial Products and Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 10.1pt;text-indent:-10.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">5</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of discount recorded by Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation on receivables sold to Financial Products and of interest earned between Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation and Financial Products.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 12.25pt;text-indent:-12.25pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">6</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of Financial Products&#146; profit due to equity method of accounting.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 12.25pt;text-indent:-12.25pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">7</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Profit attributable to common stockholders.</p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 11.5pt;text-indent:-11.5pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">1</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Represents Caterpillar Inc. and its subsidiaries with Financial Products accounted for on the equity basis.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 11.5pt;text-indent:-11.5pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">2</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of Financial Products&#146; revenues earned from Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 11.5pt;text-indent:-11.5pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">3</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of net expenses recorded by Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation paid to Financial Products.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 11.5pt;text-indent:-11.5pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">4</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of interest expense recorded between Financial Products and Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 10.1pt;text-indent:-10.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">5</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of discount recorded by Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation on receivables sold to Financial Products and of interest earned between Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation and Financial Products.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 11.5pt;text-indent:-11.5pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">6</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of Financial Products&#146; profit due to equity method of accounting.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 11.5pt;text-indent:-11.5pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">7</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Profit attributable to common stockholders.</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 11.5pt;text-indent:-11.5pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">1</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Represents Caterpillar Inc. and its subsidiaries with Financial Products accounted for on the equity basis.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 11.5pt;text-indent:-11.5pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">2</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of Financial Products&#146; revenues earned from Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 11.5pt;text-indent:-11.5pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">3</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of net expenses recorded by Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation paid to Financial Products.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 11.5pt;text-indent:-11.5pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">4</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of interest expense recorded between Financial Products and Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 10.1pt;text-indent:-10.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">5</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of discount recorded by Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation on receivables sold to Financial Products and of interest earned between Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation and Financial Products.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 11.5pt;text-indent:-11.5pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">6</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of Financial Products&#146; profit due to equity method of accounting.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 11.5pt;text-indent:-11.5pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">7</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;position:relative;top:-2.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Profit attributable to common stockholders.</p>

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Caterpillar Inc.<br> Supplemental Data for Results of Operations<br> For the Six Months Ended June&nbsp;30, 2014<br> (Unaudited)<br> (Millions of dollars)</font></b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse;">
<tr>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">1</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Represents Caterpillar Inc. and its subsidiaries with Financial Products accounted for on the equity basis.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">2</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of Financial Products&#146; revenues earned from Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">3</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of net expenses recorded by Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation paid to Financial Products.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">4</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of interest expense recorded between Financial Products and Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">5</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of discount recorded by Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation on receivables sold to Financial Products and of interest earned between Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation and Financial Products.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">6</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of Financial Products&#146; profit due to equity method of accounting.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">7</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Profit attributable to common stockholders.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">1</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Represents Caterpillar Inc. and its subsidiaries with Financial Products accounted for on the equity basis.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">2</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of Financial Products&#146; profit after tax due to equity method of accounting.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">3</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of non-cash adjustment for the undistributed earnings from Financial Products.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">4</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of non-cash adjustments and changes in assets and liabilities related to consolidated reporting.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">5</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Reclassification of Financial Products&#146; cash flow activity from investing to operating for receivables that arose from the sale of inventory.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">6</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of net proceeds and payments to/from Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation and Financial Products.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">7</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of dividend from Financial Products to Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">8</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of proceeds received from Financial Products related to Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation&#146;s sale of businesses and investments.</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">1</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Represents Caterpillar Inc. and its subsidiaries with Financial Products accounted for on the equity basis.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">2</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of Financial Products&#146; profit after tax due to equity method of accounting.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">3</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of non-cash adjustments for the undistributed earnings from Financial Products.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">4</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of non-cash adjustments and changes in assets and liabilities related to consolidated reporting.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">5</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Reclassification of Financial Products&#146; cash flow activity from investing to operating for receivables that arose from the sale of inventory.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">6</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of net proceeds and payments to/from Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation and Financial Products.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">7</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of dividend from Financial Products to Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation.</p>
<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt 15.1pt;text-indent:-15.1pt;"><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:6.5pt;position:relative;top:-3.0pt;">8</font><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font>Elimination of proceeds received from Financial Products related to Machinery, Energy&nbsp;&amp; Transportation&#146;s sale of portions of the Bucyrus distribution business to Cat dealers.</p>
